Clean it a little bit

In [4]:
ks_data.drop(["ID", "usd pledged", "currency", "goal", "pledged"], axis=1, inplace=True)
ks_data.rename(columns={"usd_pledged_real": "pleged",
                        "usd_goal_real": "goal"}, inplace=True)
ks_data['success_rate'] =  (ks_data['pleged'] / ks_data['goal'])
ks_data['country'] = ks_data['country'].replace({'US': 'United States', 
                                                 'GB': 'United Kingdom',
                                                 'AT': 'Austria',
                                                 'AU': 'Australia',
                                                 'BE': 'Belgium',
                                                 'CA': 'Canada',
                                                 'CH': 'Switzerland',
                                                 'DE': 'Germany',
                                                 'DK': 'Denmark',
                                                 'ES': 'Spain',
                                                 'FR': 'France',
                                                 'HK': 'Hong Kong',
                                                 'IE': 'Ireland',
                                                 'IT': 'Italy',
                                                 'JP': 'Japan',
                                                 'LU': 'Luxembourg',
                                                 'MX': 'Mexico',
                                                 'NL': 'Netherlands',
                                                 'SE': 'Sweden',
                                                 'SG': 'Singapore',
                                                 'NZ': 'New Zealand',
                                                 'NO': 'Norway'})

Throw out scum and anomalies

In [8]:
ks_data = ks_data[ks_data['goal'] > 1]
ks_data = ks_data[ks_data['goal'] < 1000000]
ks_data = ks_data[ks_data['backers'] < 10000]
ks_data = ks_data[ks_data['country'] != 'N,0"']

Plotting¶

In [10]:
def titles(plot, title, xlabel, ylabel):
    plot.set_title(title, fontsize=22)
    plot.set(xlabel=xlabel, ylabel = ylabel)
    plot.xaxis.label.set_size(18)
    plot.yaxis.label.set_size(18)

Project's categories

In [11]:
plt.figure(figsize = (20, 10))
top20Categories = ks_data.groupby("category").size().sort_values(ascending=False)[:20]
plot = sns.barplot(x=top20Categories.index, y=top20Categories)
titles(plot, 'Top 20 Categories', 'Category', 'Number of projects')
for item in plot.get_xticklabels():
    item.set_rotation(90)

Top 3 categories: Product Design, Documentary, Tabletop Games.

Goals

In [14]:
plt.figure(figsize = (20, 10))
plot = sns.distplot(a=ks_data[ks_data['state'].isin(['failed', 'canceled'])]['goal'], label='Unsuccessful', hist=True, kde=False, bins=int(100), color = 'grey')
plot = sns.distplot(a=ks_data[ks_data['state'] == 'successful']['goal'], label='Successful', hist=True, kde=False, bins=int(100), color = 'green')
plt.legend()
plot.set_yscale('log')
titles(plot, 'Histogram of Goals, by state', 'Goal', 'Number of projects')

Better to start inexpensive projects.

In [15]:
plt.figure(figsize = (20, 10))
ks_data_without_success_anomalies = ks_data.copy()
ks_data_without_success_anomalies = ks_data_without_success_anomalies[ks_data_without_success_anomalies['goal'] < 100000]
ks_data_without_success_anomalies = ks_data_without_success_anomalies[ks_data_without_success_anomalies['success_rate'] > 0.0001]
ks_data_without_success_anomalies = ks_data_without_success_anomalies[ks_data_without_success_anomalies['success_rate'] < 10]
ks_data_without_success_anomalies = ks_data_without_success_anomalies[ks_data_without_success_anomalies['state'].isin(['failed', 'successful'])]
plot = sns.scatterplot(x=ks_data_without_success_anomalies['goal'], y=ks_data_without_success_anomalies['success_rate'], hue=ks_data_without_success_anomalies['state'])
titles(plot, 'Success rate of Goals, with state', 'Goal', 'Success Rate')

People like multiples of 5000.

Best possibilities¶

In [16]:
plt.figure(figsize = (26, 14))
heatmap_data = pd.pivot_table(ks_data.groupby(['main_category', 'country']).mean(), 
                              values='success_rate', 
                              index=['country'], 
                              columns='main_category')
plot = sns.heatmap(data=heatmap_data, annot=True, vmax=6)
plot.set_ylim(22.0, 0)
plot.set_facecolor('black')
titles(plot, 'Average success rate by Country and Caterory', 'Category', 'Country')
plt.yticks(rotation=0)
